  "text": "Si residual values. Recent measurements of barium isotopes in the tropical North Atlantic and South Atlantic [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] have established the utility of combining Ba d and silicic acid concentrations with barium isotope measurements (δ 137/134 Ba), as the preferential incorporation of light isotopes during barite formation makes the isotopic signature of the remaining water mass sensitive to barite cycling, but unaffected by silicate cycling [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] Von Allmen et al., 2010) . In the absence of (δ 137/134 Ba) measurements, useful insights can still be made about barium cycling in this region by investigating deviation from linearity in Ba d -silicic acid relationships, and the comparison of these trends to global patterns (Fig. 6 ).",
